{
  "texts": [
    "Black holes are a fundamental prediction of Einstein's theory of general relativity.",
    "A defining feature of black holes is their event horizon, beyond which the escape velocity exceeds the speed of light, resulting in a dark compact object (Schwarzschild 1916).",
    "Furthermore, photons approaching non-rotating black holes within a critical impact parameter",
    "where G is the gravitational constant, M is the black hole mass, and c is the speed of light, significantly bend in their trajectories by large angles and cannot escape to infinity (e.g., Hilbert 1917; von Laue 1921; Bardeen 1973).",
    "The value of R c changes for spinning black holes, but within 4%."
  ]
}